Pedro is a man who was born and raised in the countryside, where the land and family are part of your life, and you live for the land and the land lives for you. He is a 44 year old farmer and is the father of adolescent children. He operates a business that was passed down in his family from generation to generation and he hopes that one of his children will take over the business in the future.

He works an incredible 14 hours per day. He moves through his fields, fertilizing them, removing pests, and performing various other tasks that make up his work day. He has always dreamed of employing people, expanding his crops, and optimizing his operations, but he has been doing this little by little due to the high costs of agricultural products that he cannot afford.

In order to achieve his goals and dreams, Pedro would like to request a loan, which he will use in the following way:
-Purchase seeds to expand his crops a little bit;
-Purchase wires to mark his territory so that he will not have conflicts with his neighbors;
-Purchase fertilizer, irrigation supplies, and hen droppings.
